    "attributes": {
        "action": "Remove the Two-Child Limit on Child Tax Credit and Universal Credit Benefits",
        "additional_details": "In a wealthy country in the 21st century, no one should be in poverty, let alone children.\r\n\r\nThe Government's two-child limit on benefits has helped push over 350,000 children into poverty last year alone.\r\n\r\nIn the middle of the worst cost of living crisis in decades, an estimated 1.5 million children will be affected this year.\r\n\r\nThis is simply unacceptable.\r\n\r\nIn a just society, there should be no need for a petition to protect children.\r\n\r\nThe two-child restriction should be reversed immediately.",
        "background": "Revoke the 6th April 2017 amendment to Child Tax Credit and Universal Credit which limits benefits to two children per family.",
